<Author>luijo100
<Content>Decent Hotel - Not so great location This hotel is actually quite an average hotel, but quite good for Amsterdam standards of budget accomodation, the rooms are a bit on the small side and the tolets are white, clean and a bit dull. The furniture in the rooms could definetly use some renovation. It's location has its ups and downs depending on what your purpose is in Amsterdam, if you are looking for something central, then skip this one as it is 20 minutes away by tram from Dam square. However the business districts of suth amsterdam are easily reached by tram. The area around the hotel is smart full of upmarket shops and some (not many) restaurants as well, but keep in mind if you are arriving late that the area is dead after 10 pm and if you want to get something to eat you'll have to go to the center of the city.Breakfast is good but seating space can be limited in the breakfast room so make sure you arrive early enough.Overall the hotel is average and a good choice if it can save you some euros. 
