<Author>Eryan99
<Content>Not outstanding but certainly good I stayed in this hotel in February 2008 for a few days.The first thing they asked us at the moment of check-in was our credit card, and we were immediately charged for the total amount of our stay. I know that sometimes this might be the policy of the hotel, but I didn't like it.Anyway, the room we got was very clean, but was SMALL!!! Even our bed was not a king size(1.60mt) but a french size(1.20mt) because probably a bigger bed couldn't fit in that small room!!!There was no place were to put your luggage, not open nor closed, and the wardrobes were not enough if you had to stay a few days. I'm not even mentioning our bathroom. you had to be a tumbler to take a shower! However, I would like to point out that the room was CLEAN and it was cleaned every day properly.The breakfast was great, and there was always tea and coffee available for free. Internet was not free but it was certainly much better than in many other places.The staff was very kind.The location is simply great, everything is easy to reach by tram from where this hotel is. 
