<Author>Aussiegirl82
<Content>Out of the ordinary experience We stayed here on business and the staff were very helpful and friendly. only a 10min walk to the WTC and 10min tram ride to Leidseplein. While we were staying there I became quite sick and stayed at the hotel during the day. They were renovating during the day. I had loud drilling noises vibrating through the rooming I was trying to sleep and recover in and I ended up in tears in my pajamas down in the lobby crying that I was sick and couldn't sleep. They immediately let me call my Mum in Australia for 20mins for FREE, moved my fiancee and I from our small 1st floor room to a large, airy rooftop room twice the size that opened on to the roof and had a rooftop view across towards Beatrix Park. I could sleep in peace without hearing any noise and the staff told me that I could go down and use the coffee machine whenever I liked. They also supplied me with a kettle to make myself soup. What a surprise for my husband when he returned back from work! I would stay here again if they weren't renovating or I could have that great rooftop room! Staff were lovely people, especially Cliff. 
