<Author>ksw430
<Content>AMS Beethoven - A great little hotel We stayed at the AMS Beethoven for 4 nights in March - loved the hotel, loved Amsterdam. The staff was very helpful and friendly. The morning we checked in, after an overnight flight, they hustled to get our room ready - by 9am - so we could anpe before hitting the city. The staff ws consistantly helpful with directions, suggestions, etc. There's a great supermarket next door, as well as a terrific bakery. The breakfast was fine - coffee excellent - and the common breakfast room was a good place to connect with other tourists. The hotel in not lavish but in a great, high-end neighborhood. The cable car stops a block from the hotel, so you can be in the center of the city in 10 minutes, yet get a bit of a feel for how real Amsterdamers live. There's a great, neighborhood Greek restaurant, Kriti, Balthazaer Floriszstrate about a 5 min walk away- towards the Museum section. We would stay there again if we can get back to Amsterdam. 
