<Content>Can't beat the location-basic but clean hotel Just back yesterday from staying at the AMS Beethovanstraat (though they are now a Ramanda). Its a basic hotel -carpet and decor is very worn but the rooms are clean, the staff is helpful and the breakfast has enough of an assortment to please most tastes. A little advice when checking in indicate you want a room located at the front of the hotel. They first tried to give us a tiny room at the back (saying it was quietier) but has a view of the garbage bins. The large rooms everyone is talking about in their reviews are all at the front of the hotel-Beethovanstraat is busy but quiets down at night. Plus you want a city view,you're in Amsterdam, after all. The location is perfect since trams make everything only minutes away and is a nice relaxing way to see the city. 
