<Content>Wonderful hospitality and amazing staff. My wife and I spent eight nights at this warm hotel. The rooms are much larger than most hotels in the centre of the city. The location is very convinient. However, the best assest the hotel has is the STAFF. Everyone from the reception desk on was warm, friendly, courteous and very helpful. It truly felt like a home away from home and it made all the difference to come back to the hotel after a long day of screenings and meetings at the documentary film festival. One of our colleauges fractured her wrist - they arranged for the hospital. I had a cast on my foot - they called the museums to see if there were wheelchairs availabel. prentations needed to be printed out - they did it without any fuss. They gave great travel tips and suggestions. Kudos to the management - they know what it means to keep their staff happy - it makes all the difference. Do stay here. 
